sections.content:
Check multiple conditions in order; only the first True branch runs.

```python
speed = 80

if speed < 40:
    print("Too slow")
elif speed <= 80:
    print("Normal speed")
else:
    print("Too fast")
```

An if inside another if for condition-inside-condition logic.

```python
logged_in = True
is_admin = False

if logged_in:
    if is_admin:
        print("Show admin panel")
    else:
        print("Show user dashboard")
else:
    print("Please log in")
```

Use nested ifs sparingly; if–elif is often clearer.
